  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd -\u0b9a\u0bae\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe \u0baa\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka must correct its mistakes - Samantha Power",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samantha Power, the CEO of USAIT, has appealed to Sri Lanka to revise the decisions that are responsible for Sri Lanka's current economic and political crisis.",
        "He said this during his visit to India and mentioned that the Biden administration and India are concerned about the economic decline of Sri Lanka and the crisis faced by the Sri Lankan people.",
        "He also mentioned that we have been holding high-level talks on how we can help the people of Sri Lanka for the past several months and we have taken important steps.",
        "He said that the 3.5 billion dollar loan provided by India is very valuable and the humanitarian development assistance provided by USAID and the assistance provided by the United States are making an important contribution.",
        "Samantha Power has also mentioned that it is essential for those who have given loans to Sri Lanka to cooperate.",
        "Samantha Power has said that it is important for the Sri Lankan government to correct the economic and political decisions made in the past - which are the cause of the current crisis.",
        "Samantha Power said that Sri Lanka's crisis was caused by various reasons including the previous government's mismanagement of funds - corruption - unwise agricultural policies - the Covid crisis and the terrorist attack that took place at the same time as Covid caused tourists not to visit Sri Lanka.",
        "The chief executive of USAIT has said that massive infrastructure projects can benefit the people of any country in the world and has also said that debt is an issue.",
        "Many countries are waiting for infrastructure projects, rightly so. Infrastructure is an important vehicle for development, Samantha Power said, but it becomes problematic over time when the cost of financing and borrowing leads to deep violations of one's own sovereignty and independence and high circular rates."
      ],
